answer.text: "The Hollywood Sign is one of the most visited attractions in the L.A. area.  There are five places where you can spot the Hollywood Sign.  Many people use the five places to see the sign.  I got close enough to see the sign without having to go all the way up to the top.  Just be careful not to park in front of the houses up in the residential neighborhood.  Also bring plenty of water, especially in the summertime.  And finally be careful when taking pictures, especially if you are standing in the middle of the street.  It is one of the many attractions that you must visit if you are in the L.A. area."

reviewSnippet.question: What are people saying about museums in Los Angeles, CA?
reviewSnippet.answerPrompt: This is a review for museums in Los Angeles, CA:

answer.text: "When I visit a friend in the area, we make it a point to go to Ten Women Gallery.  The art is made by local women, who work in many different media.  The price range is varied enough that I can find gifts as needed, or something that I would like to have in my house, from ceramics, to straw hats, to paintings, woven pieces and other creations.   The gallery is visually attractive and interesting.  It's fun to talk with the woman who is managing the gallery at the time.  The artists rotate shifts to keep it open.  I really appreciate the uniqueness, often some humor in the pieces, and shopping in a small, welcoming place.  I appreciate buying art made locally and like to support local artists."

answer.text: "It's a promising children's aquarium, but is nothing compared to the ones in the Bay or Long Beach.  Mostly an attraction for the locals.
